This is my friend Guo Jing's diary.

It records the real life experience and psychological feeling of the women who lived alone in Wuhan during the period of Fengcheng.

These words bear witness to Guo's journey from adapting to a sudden crisis to rebuilding her daily life to trying to help others.

Those who want to keep up to date can follow@guo Jing, a social worker, on Weibo.

12 February

After the sex, a feminist friend asked me if I knew about domestic violence in prostitution, and she worried, "if a woman is abused, will Jing tea still be on the police force? Will she get support? "

In the blockaded city, when a woman was subjected to domestic violence, some Jing Tea, who consider it a domestic matter, were even more reluctant to deal with such cases.

Victims are also struggling to get social support, and social services are out of work.

It was hard for her to leave home, it was hard for anyone to take her in, it was hard to get far without traffic, and hotels and hostels were closed.
Mothers and children who could only walk away from domestic violence during the epidemic control period
(photo: Xiao Meili)

My friend L said yesterday that her sister-in-law had been beaten up. The woman and the man are divorced, and they have two children, one of whom they raise. Before the Spring Festival, the man knelt in front of the woman begged her to spend the New Year with him, the children also want to spend the New Year together, crying on the side, the woman went to the man's home for the New Year. Yesterday after the woman was beaten, she firmly left the man's house with her two children and her luggage.

The woman wants to come to L's, but they're not in the same county. Because of the wind and dust, in and out of the county and village have to open a certificate, l worry that she can not out of the county, but also worry that the woman's county does not recognize the certificate, out of the county will not go back. L went with the family to get the certificate and the woman to call the police.

After the woman reported Jing, Jing Tea did not come out of Jing, but said it was OK for L and his family to pick up the woman and the child. But the man's home is also far from the border between the two counties. Unable to drive on the road, L and his family had to contact the man so that he could catch up with the woman and the Child on his tricycle and drive them to the junction of the two counties.

Finally, L and his family opened a certificate, can drive to pick up the woman. By the time they picked her up, she and her two children had been walking for four or five hours.

Last night's dinner was sauteed pork with garlic and porridge. Talking to my friends at night. Some people watch movies during the day, some people read books, some people downloaded Karaoke software in Karaoke.

We talked about a lot of things in the news over the past two days about not rich old people donating money, such as a retired sanitation worker who gave away 100,000 of his savings from years of saving, leaving only 13.78 on his card. We're all sad, not moved.

WILL THEIR DONATIONS BE PROPERLY DISTRIBUTED? IS SOCIETY WORTHY OF THEIR DONATIONS? If one day they get sick, will the social security system guarantee them medical treatment and care? Some people suspect that the news is intended to induce people to give money, but many people are not reluctant to give money, but care about who the money goes to.

A retired sanitation worker who gave away his life savings

Let's just talk about old age. Some people say: "In the countryside, the social circle of the elderly is mainly relatives and neighbors. " Some people say: My Grandmother Lives in the city, often to get free health care products, she is more savvy, only to get free health care products, but there are a lot of old people out there who get cheated,"he says.

Some people mentioned that some people in Hangzhou rent in their own house, and other elderly people living together, there will be different habits of the problem, communication problems. But the same thing happens when we share a house with someone else now, and that's a stumbling block in our daily lives.

We know less about the elderly and generally imagine that the elderly are not energetic, and out of touch with society. In fact, old age also needs to be redefined. Age varies from person to person, and people in rural areas are more likely to age because many people do manual work and spend years outside.

Unfortunately, because of the relative surplus of labour, it is difficult for older people in cities to find jobs once they reach retirement age. But many older people don't want to just be stuck at home. They want to expand their lives as much as possible. Many old people dance in the square and travel around if they can afford it.

A broomstick on Feb. 12(image courtesy of Xiao Meili)

Yesterday, a lot of people in my friends' circle posted a video of the broomstick, because some people said that "NASA said that because of the perfect gravity angle of the earth today, it is the only day that the broom can stand alone. " Friends said at first that they were a little skeptical, but it's amazing when you try it and it works. Depending on the condition of the broom itself, the wider and heavier any object, the greater the chance of standing. This kind of news is usually believed, but now everyone has more time and curiosity to try.

Because yesterday, Wu Han began to all the closed management of the community, originally thought today to continue to go out to understand the situation, I think a lot of reasons. I woke up this morning feeling extremely tired. Exercise was supposed to be a wake-up call, but I got lost and finished it. The morning is cloudy, I more do not have the motive that go out, gave oneself put a holiday.

The 074 hotline recently received two inquiries about sexual assault, and my partner and I did some discussion and analysis of the cases. I briefly returned to my normal life.

The Sun came out of nowhere. At 5 pm, I looked out of the window, outside the sun is very good, the opposite floor someone drying quilt, downstairs there is a family like just back from the supermarket, from the car took several bags of things.

13 February

Someone asked me about the difference between writing a diary now and doing the kind of work I used to do to help others. This is a very interesting question, the difference between the two is that I am a witness to the sweat and dust. In my previous work, I had supported others, and although I knew a little about the sexism and gender violence they suffered, I was never a witness. Now I am still a doer and a witness.

I'm telling people what I know, and I'm telling them what I know. This narrative must have some degree of self-disclosure, exposing my powerlessness, my exhaustion, my anger, my struggle and resistance. Public speaking also inevitably invites scrutiny and commentary.

But victims of gender discrimination and gender violence face these problems when they speak out about their experiences, and many of them still choose to speak out. It wasn't easy, and I tried to be honest.

Yesterday's dinner was lettuce stir-fried with meat and Rice gruel. Talking to my friends at night. Some went to feed their cats during the day, some bought food for the people on duty at the village gate, and some watched a video of a judicial exam.

We're talking about conflict. People are afraid of conflict, especially violence, and some of them can't handle the feeling of losing control in a conflict, some of them feel threatened by violence, some of them feel powerless in the face of conflict.

Several people spoke of being abused as a child, of being subjected to violence that was out of control, of being scared and powerless because her father was emotionally unpredictable, and of being subjected to "rational violence. " Parents beat their children when they don't finish eating or go to bed on time, leaving her to wonder if she did something wrong.

When we were kids, we'd just curl up in a corner in the face of violence. But now that we're adults, some of US still say we don't know what to do in the face of violence, like we're frozen. Many women are frozen at the moment of being sexually harassed and don't know how to react. It's a sign of weakness.

Why is this happening? Women are not encouraged by society to express anger, to lose their temper. When a woman loses her temper, she is called a shrew. A shrew is a slur on a woman. This slur is even worse than saying that a man is a domestic bully. It is hard for women to express their anger to others and society. Many women have to bear it in silence and grieve alone.

Some say she uses cold violence in the face of conflict, but feels more like she's punishing herself than others. Women are less likely to express dissatisfaction directly, which takes practice. Sometimes, we will be in the imagination of the mouth to quarrel, but in reality always stutter.

Some people say it's more aggressive to fight in your native language or dialect. Of course, I'm not encouraging people to fight, but I'm thinking and practicing how to express themselves in a conflict.

An isolated area covered in sweat on Feb. 13(photo provided by Guo Jing)

When I went out in the morning, the sun was just breaking through the clouds and hitting the ground. When I went out, the security guard didn't stop me, didn't ask me, and I felt lucky to be free to go out. Yesterday, a friend asked me what I lack now, I do not have any thinking, blurted out "lack of freedom. ".

After the dust, the city's streets no noise, you can hear the birds. An old man was playing Tai Chi on the side of a building. The supermarket began to control people's entry. The line started from five or six meters away from the door. There was a distance of one meter between people.

There was a table for the community workers at one of the intersections, with a thermometer and hand sanitizer on the table, and there were eight or nine people, two of them sitting behind the table. An old man was talking to two people, one of whom was wearing a red hat reserved for community workers.

After a while, the old man left and I went over to ask her what was wrong. "My wife needs to go to the hospital to see a doctor and prescribe medicine, but it's not pneumonia, it's cerebral hemorrhage, he needs to go to the hospital once a month, " she said anxiously. "I don't know. He can't walk to the hospital and the community doesn't give him a car. "

The pills her husband takes are prescription only. They're hard to get. Standing in front of five people in uniform, the old man went to tell them their situation, the man in uniform said: "This or looking for the community. " The old man reluctantly left.

People Communicating with the Community Service Center (picture provided by Guo Jing)

The uniformed men were here to watch a few vegetable sellers close their stalls. The greengrocer was discontented and murmured. They may also be facing livelihood problems, so they have to come out to make money. In fact, their stall location is relatively open, compared with the supermarket airtight space, but more to avoid the spread of the virus. But they're being evicted.

At the gate of the residential area and the intersection of the village in the city there are more people wearing red hats and writing "do not go out to prevent disease, to safely control the door. ". These placards look like the uniform print.

This kind of propaganda is easy to carry out uniformly. I stopped at an intersection to take a picture. Red Cap, sitting on a stool, was very alert. I stood up immediately. "What are you doing? " I said impatiently. "take a picture. "

"Are you a journalist? "

"No, I live nearby. "

Unified Slogan (picture provided by Guo Jing)

Outside the community health center, two men in protective suits, masks and goggles were talking to an old man. I didn't dare get too close.

On the way there were two new observation posts, one of which had isolated two adjacent hotels, and several people at the door took off their protective clothing and disinfected themselves with yellow spray boxes.

Passing a small supermarket, the door with an empty vegetable basket blocked, shopping people in the outside to choose things, cashiers in the door settlement. Someone was entering one of the neighborhoods, and she was holding a piece of paper, and she was showing it to a security guard, probably a key card.

In the afternoon, the building opposite the power supply bureau plays music loudly with the sound box, is that kind of many stores in order to attract customers feeling, usually every store is playing, it will be very noisy, now a place is playing, a bit rare.

Customers are banned from the supermarket on Feb. 13(photo provided by Guo Jing)

14 February

Can we go out? It's not up to US anymore. I'm covered in sweat, but luckily, I'm still out of the house. A lot of places restrict access to the neighborhood.

A friend in a county town in Hubei Province said her neighborhood had been restricted for several days, with a community notice yesterday saying it was completely off limits, not even for food.

Yesterday morning, her family rushed out to buy vegetables with masks and passes. Many people grabbed vegetables at the vegetable market. When her family went to buy potatoes, a person in front of her was going to buy all the potatoes. Her family asked him to keep some, her family just bought a few potatoes. In the afternoon, her family wants to go out again to buy some things to be unable to leave the community. This is like the routine in Wuhan when the wind and dust, the temporary announcement, did not tell residents how to get protection of life.

In dealing with infectious diseases, Z has to take people's fears into account, in addition to controlling the virus itself. But on the contrary, some places began to encourage reporting, reporting a new coronavirus pneumonia patients reward 10,000 yuan, the patient will go to the hospital will reward some money.

PEOPLE'S TRUST IN Z, trust between people is constantly being consumed, panic is being strengthened. In recent days, the area has become more controlled, the number of people allowed into the supermarket, the number of sealed off areas around it, and more isolated areas. And when a lot of people need help, community workers, people in uniform are incompetent. I felt a deep sense of despair.

Last night's dinner was mushroom and pork with Rice gruel. Talk to your friends after dinner. Some people are learning English, we share some learning experience, in general to use, listen to and watch English articles and programs. Of course, speaking is also very important, we learn English process encountered difficulties.

"learning a language is not just a skill, it's a culture, " says Ito, a Japanese journalist who has traveled to cities across China to share her story in the black box, a book about her experiences with sexual assault, a friend who attended her event said that Ito was particularly humble when she spoke Japanese and powerful when she spoke English.

Now that we're all staying at home, we're talking about some kind of nerd culture. Many stay at home workers, some of whom have full time jobs, may have uncreative jobs like screws or jobs arranged by their parents. Fat Fat spends a lot of time playing games. They like the second dimension. The game and the two dimensional culture are full of sexism, presenting women as sexual objects. Many of the fatties live with their parents, and even their parents provide care for them.

This is a passive resistance to society, because the class is fixed, young people lack the opportunity to try and make mistakes, many people do not see the room for improvement, it is a kind of "effort is useless" despair.

But women still can not afford to stay at home, society has never let women easily be taken care of, if women idle at home, forced marriage pressure is greater, women at home do not do housework will also be criticized. A lot of people are starting to escape gender, the man does not want to bear the social burden of supporting his family, the woman does not want to be a "good wife and mother" to take care of the family.

People wait in line outside a supermarket on Feb. 13
(image courtesy of Guo Jing)

Some say she dreamt last night that she was hiding in her dream without a mask. We talked about dreams. Many people have had dreams about examinations, dreams are often not ready to take the exam, or when the exam to copy others can not copy. From time to time I dream of myself back to junior high school, the dream is always worried about the test. The exam will have a result, which can be used to judge whether we are good students or not. We've been carrying this burden since we were kids.

After College, we may not have to pass exams to prove ourselves, but there will still be times when we are suspicious of ourselves and seem to need standards to prove ourselves. In fact, a certain achievement can determine a person's life is very sad, but our society is such.

I was the first college student in my village, and I thought it was very lucky for me to go to college. After I went to college, I started reading books on sociology, focusing on social issues, taking part in activities, and meeting like-minded people, my world is expanding.

A few of us even dream about toilets. Some people dream of going to the toilet but can not find the toilet, sometimes it is really urgent to pee, sometimes it seems to be some kind of anxiety. There's a sense of shame when someone goes to the bathroom in a dream in front of a lot of people.

I occasionally dream of junior high school toilet, it is behind the teaching building, the light is blocked, very dark. There were no stalls, just a row of pits, about twenty or thirty, for about a thousand people. It rains in summer, the toilet begins to have seeper, want every paragraph of distance mat a brick steps into. There's GonNa be a lot of maggots in the summer, and it's GonNa be impossible to go to the bathroom without stepping on them. It was dirty. It was a place I wanted to escape.

February 14th, outside the window
(image courtesy of Guo Jing)

Today about eight o'clock it rained, the rain is very loud, I got up. I opened the window, the breeze blowing, did not feel cold, but a kind of cool. I don't know when the weather started to change. I leaned against the window and stood there for a long time.

Downstairs. Someone's driving out. There were very few people on the road. I was wondering if I wanted to go out today. Going out every day is no longer a must, but there is no plan. It is a temporary decision.

Every day may be the last day to go out, I fear really can not go out I will regret, but today is more important. I had a lot of work to do, but it didn't seem urgent. I didn't realize I was getting a little delayed in this situation. Finally, I did not go out, from some trivial work to start, slowly settle down.

15 February

The magic of reality is always beyond imagination. In the morning I saw an article titled "someone bought a batch of face masks, the delivery place is Hannan Workers Culture Palace of Wuhan Federation of Trade Unions" . After the masks were sold out everywhere, the article said, some people formed a group buying group to find all kinds of channels to buy them. A wechat merchant said there was a batch of Japanese masks exported from the Henan Factory. After the mask was issued, the logistics display was issued from Wuhan. The delivery box said "relief supplies" . The article was quickly deleted, but the offending microblog remained, with one commenter writing that 10,000 masks bought by a friend had also been shipped from Wuhan.

In the afternoon, the Wuhan Development Zone tweeted a rumor that the sender had used an alias and had nothing to do with the Hannan Workers'Cultural Palace of the Wuhan Federation of Trade Unions. The masks were produced by Wuhan Huashida Protective Products Co. , Ltd. , not donated by the public. Wuhan Huashida Protective Products Co. , Ltd. . The address is No. 511, Weihu road, Hannan Shama, near the former "Hannan Culture Palace" .

Courier pick-up, location "Wuhan Huashida Protective Products Co. , Ltd. " near the time, Josiah Goddard map electronic map location of the postal address "Wuhan Federation of Trade Unions Hannan Workers Culture Palace" . The courier confirmed it. But it still doesn't explain why it says "relief supplies. ". I asked SF express on February 2, the courier said Wuhan can not be sent to the outside express.

In a satirical video that went viral the other day on Friendagenda, a Rolex goes home, an entrepreneur buys 100,000 masks and donates them. As the box is sealed, the Rolex watch falls into the box. The mask was transported to the place responsible for the distribution of goods and materials was taken by the leadership to set off the bill and sent to the president of the Andrology Hospital. Someone from the hospital bought the masks and sold them to a wechat business. After several sales, the entrepreneur bought back the masks, unpacked the boxes and found his rolex. In the process of reselling, everybody also makes money by understating the price. The video ends with the words: This story is fictional and I would be honored if there were any similarities.

A Rolex on the way home

Yesterday's dinner was sauteed pork with cabbage and Rice gruel. Talking to my friends at night.

Several friends have started to go to bed early, some will go to bed early and get up early, some will go to bed early and still get up late. Some people say: "The body is escaping the stress and trauma of reality. "

A friend said that her sister likes to compare with her, in many ways, such as academic performance, making friends. The younger sister is dissatisfied with the results of the comparison, so she quarrels with her friends and emotionally punishes them. When we don't find what we value, we like to compare ourselves to others, see what others have that we don't, and feel inferior, jealous, or unfair as a result. Comparison is social, we are being compared from an early age, academic performance, whether there are strengths, family background and so on.

Some people grow up not buying clothes. Several people agreed. When buying clothes will often be evaluated, by parents, friends, guides, etc. , always someone said you here fat where thick, very uncomfortable.

My friends and I are now relatively free of the constraints of mainstream society on women. When we talked about the relative mainstream, we shared the mainstream, and we all had long hair. At that time, people also wear high heels, some people wear 9 cm high heels. A friend said: "everyone mainstream when there is no characteristics, now more personality. "

Several of US started growing our hair long after college, because shorter hair in middle school and high school saves time and is better for learning. In middle school and high school, the school will control the students'clothes and hairstyle, trousers and skirts should be above the knees, and the hair should not be dyed. When I was in high school, one of my female classmates had curly hair. The teacher was suspicious of it and insisted that she straighten her hair.

When we talk about makeup, several people have tried light makeup. A good woman should wear light make-up to look innocent. Someone said: "It takes courage to put on a lot of makeup. Only when you are confident can you put on a lot of makeup. "

At about ten o'clock last night the thunder began to rumble out of the window, and I opened it; it was blowing, and there was a heavy rain. Outside my window there is a Sunshade, the rain still hit the window, knock knock. When I was a child, I loved the rain, because when it rained, I didn't have to work on the ground. I could sleep or play in the warm bed. The storm at this moment is like a warning, the Earth's warning to mankind once again. Friends said: "COVID-19, earthquakes, bird flu, cold waves, locusts, this series of disasters like the Earth's attack on human beings. "

As I lay in bed, the clanging outside was the sound of the rain on the temporary guardrail of the construction site, plus the sound of the rain on the windows. I want to have the power of a storm. The noise last night made me fall asleep for a long time. I didn't get up until after nine today. It was still raining outside, and the temporary guardrails on the construction site were blown out in some places. The window fogged up and we couldn't see out. It's the best time to stay indoors in this weather.

A guardrail is blown over downstairs on Feb. 15(photo provided by Guo Jing) 

In the afternoon, I found that the outside of my house was leaking, and water was seeping into it. There was a socket right where the water was seeping. At the time, I was using that outlet. I told my friends in the chat group about this situation. One friend said, "see if you can find the strobe button that controls this socket. Try it with a small appliance. " I went to try it. She called me right away, worried I'd try the socket and get electrocuted.

The switch has three switch buttons, a Tube Room and toilet socket, a tube air conditioning socket, a tube kitchen socket. I turned off the button that ran the room and the bathroom outlet, and the light went out. Fortunately, the previous occupant had left behind an old desk lamp, which is now the only lighting fixture in the room.

I told the landlord about the leak, and the landlord asked me to talk to the property. It's not an emergency. The estate won't care now.

A wall socket leaking water (picture provided by Guo Jing)

Afternoon snow, as a northerner in the south in recent years rarely see snow, I thought I can take a look at the snow, went downstairs. I saw the property door closed, thought no one, go to the guard room to ask about the property. To the community's door, I have not opened, security stopped me, said: "Now only to see a doctor and work can go out, to the property card. " I asked: "How to buy food? "

"You can buy vegetables, but only if you have a pass. "

"When did you stop going out? "

"from today, the city will issue a notice. "

I went to the property again, knocked on the door, someone opened the door, there are three staff. I told them about the leak in the house, and one of the staff said they didn't care, and the landlord had to fix it himself.

At this time, there are two old people from the building I live out, with the property people said to go out quarantine, said it is suspected cases, a property people took them out of the community. I was shocked. At that time I was anxious to confirm with the property people out of the matter, did not ask them about the situation.

I asked people in the community, "how do I get a pass to buy food? "
"every three days. "
"I just came downstairs and I'm wearing this mask. Can I go out and buy some food? "
"Don't go out for that. "
I had to go upstairs.

Yesterday's dinner was sauteed pork with cabbage and Rice gruel. Talking to my friends at night.

Several friends have started to go to bed early, some will go to bed early and get up early, some will go to bed early and still get up late. Some people say: "The body is escaping the stress and trauma of reality. "

A friend said that her sister likes to compare with her, in many ways, such as academic performance, making friends. The younger sister is dissatisfied with the results of the comparison, so she quarrels with her friends and emotionally punishes them. When we don't find what we value, we like to compare ourselves to others, see what others have that we don't, and feel inferior, jealous, or unfair as a result. Comparison is social, we are being compared from an early age, academic performance, whether there are strengths, family background and so on.

Some people grow up not buying clothes. Several people agreed. When buying clothes will often be evaluated, by parents, friends, guides, etc. , always someone said you here fat where thick, very uncomfortable.

My friends and I are now relatively free of the constraints of mainstream society on women. When we talked about the relative mainstream, we shared the mainstream, and we all had long hair. At that time, people also wear high heels, some people wear 9 cm high heels. A friend said: "everyone mainstream when there is no characteristics, now more personality. "

Several of US started growing our hair long after college, because shorter hair in middle school and high school saves time and is better for learning. In middle school and high school, the school will control the students'clothes and hairstyle, trousers and skirts should be above the knees, and the hair should not be dyed. When I was in high school, one of my female classmates had curly hair. The teacher was suspicious of it and insisted that she straighten her hair.

When we talk about makeup, several people have tried light makeup. A good woman should wear light make-up to look innocent. Someone said: "It takes courage to put on a lot of makeup. Only when you are confident can you put on a lot of makeup. "

At about ten o'clock last night the thunder began to rumble out of the window, and I opened it; it was blowing, and there was a heavy rain. Outside my window there is a Sunshade, the rain still hit the window, knock knock. When I was a child, I loved the rain, because when it rained, I didn't have to work on the ground. I could sleep or play in the warm bed. The storm at this moment is like a warning, the Earth's warning to mankind once again. Friends said: "COVID-19, earthquakes, bird flu, cold waves, locusts, this series of disasters like the Earth's attack on human beings. "

As I lay in bed, the clanging outside was the sound of the rain on the temporary guardrail of the construction site, plus the sound of the rain on the windows. I want to have the power of a storm. The noise last night made me fall asleep for a long time. I didn't get up until after nine today. It was still raining outside, and the temporary guardrails on the construction site were blown out in some places. The window fogged up and we couldn't see out. It's the best time to stay indoors in this weather.

A guardrail is blown over downstairs on Feb. 15(photo provided by Guo Jing) 

In the afternoon, I found that the outside of my house was leaking, and water was seeping into it. There was a socket right where the water was seeping. At the time, I was using that outlet. I told my friends in the chat group about this situation. One friend said, "see if you can find the strobe button that controls this socket. Try it with a small appliance. " I went to try it. She called me right away, worried I'd try the socket and get electrocuted.

The switch has three switch buttons, a Tube Room and toilet socket, a tube air conditioning socket, a tube kitchen socket. I turned off the button that ran the room and the bathroom outlet, and the light went out. Fortunately, the previous occupant had left behind an old desk lamp, which is now the only lighting fixture in the room.

I told the landlord about the leak, and the landlord asked me to talk to the property. It's not an emergency. The estate won't care now.

Afternoon snow, as a northerner in the south in recent years rarely see snow, I thought I can take a look at the snow, went downstairs. I saw the property door closed, thought no one, go to the guard room to ask about the property. To the community's door, I have not opened, security stopped me, said: "Now only to see a doctor and work can go out, to the property card. " I asked: "How to buy food? "

"You can buy vegetables, but only if you have a pass. "

"When did you stop going out? "

"from today, the city will issue a notice. "

I went to the property again, knocked on the door, someone opened the door, there are three staff. I told them about the leak in the house, and one of the staff said they didn't care, and the landlord had to fix it himself.

At this time, there are two old people from the building I live out, with the property people said to go out quarantine, said it is suspected cases, a property people took them out of the community. I was shocked. At that time I was anxious to confirm with the property people out of the matter, did not ask them about the situation.

I asked people in the community, "how do I get a pass to buy food? "
"every three days. "
"I just came downstairs and I'm wearing this mask. Can I go out and buy some food? "
"Don't go out for that. "
I had to go upstairs.
